The term '''avunculate''' refers to the relationship between a man and his sister's children, generally her sons.  In certain tribal peoples (example: the [[Korowai]]), '''avunculate''' refers to a special relation ship between a man and a maternal uncle, and the mutual responsibilities between them.

The English word ''avuncular'' is an adjective defined as "of or pertaining to an uncle." It descends from the Latin word ''avunculus'', which means "uncle."

